Pursuing an Orwellian logic, the latter claims that the world's largest gold company has filed a six million defamation lawsuit against three authors and a small publishing house squabbled with the intention of initiating a "transparent public debate".
If it is true that judges are independent and impartial, it is not the truth that they judge, especially in the case of a defamation complaint, but the law.
